'''''Rendezvous with Rama''''' is an [[interactive fiction]]<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Murphy |first=Jamie |others=Reported by Cristina Garcia |title=Stepping into the Story: Players participate in 'interactive fiction' |magazine=Time |date=May 13, 2013 |volume=125 |number=19 |page=64 |quote=A version of ''Rendezvous with Rama'' is available in interactive form on a floppy disk (Telarium $39.95).}}</ref> game with graphics published by [[Telarium]], a subsidiary of [[Spinnaker Software]], in 1984. It was developed in cooperation with [[Arthur C. Clarke]] and based upon his 1973 science fiction novel ''[[Rendezvous with Rama]]''.

==Reception==
German reviewers recognized the complexity of the storyline and the various possibilities of interaction with [[non-player character]]s.<ref>Boris Schneider-Johne, Heinrich Lenhardt: ''Science Fiction-Adventures'', Happy Computer 5/1985, p.145ff.</ref>

